HEADWORD: Phosphorous
<hw>Phos"phor*ous</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocr⟧s"f⟦ocr⟧r*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>phosphoreux</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of
or pertaining to phosphorus; resembling or containing phosphorus;
specifically, designating those compounds in which phosphorus has a
lower valence as contrasted with <contr>phosphoric</contr> compounds;
<as>as, <ex>phosphorous</ex> acid,
<chform>H3PO3</chform></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

